questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a custom caching component built on top of `ConcurrentHashMap` fails to retrieve stored entries after updates, causing orphan entries and eventual `OutOfMemoryError` heap exhaustion. The following method is invoked during high concurrent traffic:

java
public class MetricsCache {
    private final Map<MetricKey, MetricValue> cache = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();

    public void updateMetric(MetricKey key, double val) {
        MetricValue value = cache.computeIfAbsent(key, k -> new MetricValue());
        value.addSample(val);
        key.setTimestamp(System.currentTimeMillis());
    }
}
